# Unofficial Cursor News — Feed Service Plan (Phases 1–7)

Build the **Unofficial Cursor News** app feed service through **vertical slices** (shippable user value per phase) and **modularity** (single-responsibility modules inside each slice).

**Product name:** Unofficial Cursor News  
**Positioning:** Unofficial fan app — **not affiliated with Anysphere.**  
**Brand copy:** Refer to the product as **Cursor** (not "Cursor AI").  
**Stack:** `api` (Node ingest + JSON API) + `mobile` (Expo Dev Client). Optional `web/` for browser preview.

**Out of scope:** Phase 8 (native Swift/iOS without Expo) — do not plan or implement unless user explicitly requests.

---

## Architecture (always)

```
Sources (registry) → Ingest → Normalize → Store → API routes → Mobile/Web client → Open original URL
```

| Module | Path | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| Source registry | `api/src/sources/registry.js` | Allowlisted feeds; enable/disable; ingest method |
| Ingest | `api/src/ingest/feeds.js`, `scrape.js` | Pull RSS/Atom/scrape (metadata only) |
| Normalize | `api/src/normalize/news-item.js` | `NewsItem` shape, excerpt cap, dedupe keys |
| Store | `api/src/store/` | Cache (memory → DB later) |
| Routes | `api/src/index.js` | HTTP only — no ingest logic inline |
| Mobile API client | `mobile/src/api/newsClient.js` | Fetch JSON — no RSS, no UI |
| Screens | `mobile/App.js` or `mobile/src/screens/` | UI only — calls API client |

**Ethics (every phase):** title + short excerpt (≤300 chars) + canonical URL + attribution. Tap opens original in browser. Never republish full article body in-app.

**Four ingest paths (expand in Phase 3):** (1) RSS/Atom, (2) scrape API fallback, (3) curated registry, (4) third-party aggregator feeds.

---

## Phase 1 — Core feed (official sources)

**Vertical slice:** User sees Cursor changelog + GitHub releases on device; tap opens original.

**Sources (registry, enabled):**
- `https://cursor.com/changelog/rss.xml` (changelog RSS — canonical URL in `registry.js`)
- `https://github.com/getcursor/cursor/releases.atom` (may be empty upstream)

**API:** `GET /v1/news`, `GET /v1/sources`, `POST /v1/ingest`, `GET /v1/status`, `GET /health`. Bootstrap ingest on startup when cache empty.

**Dev TLS (Zscaler):** `node --use-system-ca` in `api/package.json` `dev`/`start` scripts.

**Mobile:** Feed list, refresh (ingest + reload), disclaimer banner, open link via `Linking.openURL`. Physical Android: `adb reverse tcp:8787 tcp:8787` or `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE`.

**Done when:** Refresh returns real items; every card opens a valid external URL; disclaimer visible.

**Do not:** scraping, aggregators, payments, push, UI polish.

---

## Phase 2 — Dedupe + registry quality

**Vertical slice:** One clean timeline — duplicate stories appear once.

**Work:** `dedupeNewsItems` by canonical URL; official source wins over aggregator when added later. Sort by `publishedAt` desc. Expose source metadata on `GET /v1/sources`.

**Done when:** Same story from two sources shows once; registry is the single place to add sources.

**Do not:** change mobile UI layout beyond what dedupe requires.

---

## Phase 3 — Expand coverage (four ingest paths)

**Vertical slice:** More Cursor news sources, same rules.

**Add incrementally (one source at a time, test each):**
1. RSS/Atom — forum/community feeds if available
2. Scrape — `scrape.js` behind env flag; metadata only; robots/ToS respect
3. Registry — new rows in `registry.js` (later DB)
4. Aggregators — e.g. Releasebot Cursor RSS (`enabled: false` until verified)

**Done when:** ≥2 ingest methods live; each source documented in registry with `ingestMethod`, `attributionLabel`, `maxExcerptChars`.

**Do not:** full-page scrape storage; paywalled content republishing.

---

## Phase 4 — UX essentials (functional, not beautiful)

**Vertical slice:** Daily-usable reader on Windows + phone.

**Work:** loading/error states; category filter (All, Changelog, Releases, Blog, Forum); About panel (unofficial notice, how sources work); empty state; API-down hint with dev commands.

**Done when:** User can filter, refresh, and understand unofficial status without confusion.

**Do not:** animations, custom themes, marketing polish.

---

## Phase 5 — Notifications

**Vertical slice:** User gets alerted when **new** items appear (opt-in).

**Work:** scheduled ingest job (`api/src/jobs/`); diff new vs last run; device token registration endpoint; Expo push or web push (PWA path via `web/` if needed). Per-category toggles: Changelog, Releases, Blog. Default digest; instant = Pro later (Phase 6).

**Done when:** New changelog entry triggers notification user subscribed to; mute/opt-out works.

**Do not:** spam; notify on duplicates; push unrelated marketing.

---

## Phase 6 — Membership ($1–$5/mo)

**Vertical slice:** Optional support — **core news stays free.**

| Tier | Price | Free | Paid |
|---|---|---|---|
| Core feed + open originals | $0 | ✅ | ✅ |
| Advanced filters / saved items | — | basic | ✅ |
| Notification modes (instant vs digest) | — | digest | ✅ |

**Work:** Stripe/web billing module (not in mobile bundle secrets); gate **convenience only**, never headlines or links.

**Done when:** Free users retain full feed; members get extras only.

**Do not:** paywall news; external payment CTAs that violate store rules without IAP where required.

---

## Phase 7 — Ship web + PWA

**Vertical slice:** Public URL; add-to-home-screen; production API.

**Work:** Deploy API (Railway/Fly/Render/etc.); deploy Expo EAS or static `web/` build (Netlify/Vercel); env-based `API_BASE`; PWA manifest + service worker shell; Privacy Policy + DMCA/opt-out page.

**Done when:** Public URL works on phone browser; ingest runs on schedule in production; disclaimer + attribution on every item.

**Do not:** go live without privacy/DMCA pages; expose scrape API keys client-side.

---

## Agent workflow per phase

1. **Research** target slice files before coding.
2. **Implement vertical slice** end-to-end (API + client for that slice).
3. **Verify** on Windows: API `npm run dev` + mobile `npx expo start --dev-client` (or web `npm run dev`).
4. Ask user: **"Ezequiel, is the implementation successful?"** before SUCCESS logs or branch commit.
5. **One phase at a time** — do not skip ahead unless user approves.

